# Project Definition Template

This rule serves as a template for defining the project context, including its purpose, technical stack, folder structure, customizations, and libraries.

<rule>
name: project_definition
description: Enforce project context definition for CursorAI
filters:
  - type: file_extension
    pattern: "\\.md$"
  - type: file_path
    pattern: "README.md|/docs/"

actions:
  - type: enforce
    conditions:
      - pattern: "## Project Purpose"
        message: "Define the purpose of the project in the README file."

      - pattern: "## Technical Stack"
        message: "List the technical stack used in the project in the README file."

      - pattern: "## Folder Structure"
        message: "Document the folder structure in the README file."

      - pattern: "## Customizations"
        message: "Include any custom themes, modules, or libraries in the README file."

      - pattern: "## Libraries"
        message: "List any third-party libraries used in the project in the README file."

  - type: suggest
    message: |
      Project Definition Best Practices:
      - Search for the README file and /docs/ folder to gather context.
      - Clearly define the project's purpose and goals.
      - Specify the technical stack and versions used.
      - Document the folder structure for easy navigation.
      - Include details about custom themes and modules.
      - List any libraries and their versions for dependency management.

  - type: validate
    conditions:
      - pattern: "## Project Purpose"
        message: "Ensure the project purpose is clearly defined."

      - pattern: "## Technical Stack"
        message: "Ensure the technical stack is documented."

      - pattern: "## Folder Structure"
        message: "Ensure the folder structure is outlined."

      - pattern: "## Customizations"
        message: "Ensure customizations are documented."

      - pattern: "## Libraries"
        message: "Ensure libraries are listed."

metadata:
  priority: medium
  version: 1.0
</rule> 